<a id="introduction"></a>
<h4>Introduction</h4>

Ordering Management System, OMS in the future, was developed to handle ordering of car models by different categories of clients including retailers and distributors. While ordering is done exclusively by clients, that is users that have 'client' role assigned to them, system itself is managed by 2 privileged roles: "stff" and "administrator".
This section of the help file describes functionality available to staff members (see <%= link_to "User Categories", "#user_categories" %> below) 

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="user_categories"></a>
<h4>User Categories</h4>
There are 5 categories of users in OMS:
<ul>
  <li>
  -user : anybody who registers online with ability to only look at the products available.
  </li>
  <li>
  -client : Anybody who is registered as a client, and there are 5 different client categoies, will be able to see products and order them
  <li>
  - production: manufacturing facility will be able to see current order situation and deal with shipments and inventories
  </li>
  <li>
  - staff : can do everything, but change other user's profiles and privileges as well as modify orders
  </li>
  <li>
  - admin: full control if the system
  </li>
</ul>

