<a id="workflow"></a>
<h4>Workflow</h4>

As a staff member, you have privileges to create and modify client profiles (see Clients section in Menu Description pages below) as well as product information.
Clients can be set up using 2 different scenarios:

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<b>Scenario 1</b>
<ul>
<li> - If client is not in database yet, create new client record in 'Clients' index page by clicking on "Add Client" button and filling out all required information. It's important to have all basic contact information filled out as it will be later used to generate documents such as Puchase Orders and Invoices. Make sure to add email address of the client.</li>
<li> - Send an invitation to client to register by clicking on the icon in "invite" column in client list for this client. </li>
<li> - Client receives an invitation and goes to SignUp page to register. </li>
<li> - Client activates his account by clicking activation link sent to him in email and because this email address is already registered in the system as client, no further action on your part is required </li>
</ul>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<b>Scenario 2</b>
<ul>
  <li> - Client visits the website and registers as unprivileged user. This user becomes active after client activates new registration by following the link sent to them in registration email </li>
  <li> - You, as a staff member receive email notification about new user registration. </li>
  <li> - You recognize the new user as a client and from user menu modify their profile, where you assign 'client' role to the new user and select client name from the list of known clients </li>
</ul>
After 'client' role is assigned to the user, they can log into the system and order products.  

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="ordering"></a>
<h4>Ordering</h4>

Ordering is done by registered clients. So, if you want to make an order on client's behalf you will need to switch to this client's user profile in Users menu by clicking on <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-random"> </i> &nbsp; icon in user row. After you switch, you will see client's name in the header and client's email will show up as logged in user in the footer.
<p>
There are two ways to order products: directly from product list, by entering number for each selected product, or by goling to Orders page and clicking on <Add Product To Cart> button at the bottom. In both cases, entered number of selected product will be added to shopping cart, which whill show as a shopping cart symbol and number in upper right corner of the page. Once selection is finished and all products are added to shopping cart, you can finalize the order by first clicking on shopping cart symbol which will open shopping cart modal, where you can either submit order or empty shopping cart and start from the beginning. 
<p>
Once order is submitted several things will happen: 

<ul>
<li> - Inventory is updated: number of available products is automatically reduced by the ordered number </li>
<li> - Emails are sent: Order confirmation email to the user, Order notification to staff members and  Low quantity notification to staff if number of available products is nevative </li>
<li> - PO and Invoice for the new order are generated and order is assigned 'Pending' status </li>
</ul>


